column5: Too tired for very long report but in short the main stuff...fished in 89fow with couple very good buddies from 9am till 1pm...got my limit by 11am...whities caught on Williams Half/half and one on minnow line. JJ got one laker as well. Not sure how they have doneafter I left. Extremely hard walk....especially on the way back...tons of snow...more then foot and it was snowing all morning. Beautiful nice and white though... Must get myself snowmobile soon...getting old for those 6-7km/day walking trips loaded with full gear and in foot of snow. Few pictures  for your viewing pleasure... Took them with my cell phone so not the best quality but you can get the idea Thanks for the great company Husky and JJ.
Nice work guys!! Those are beauty fish!  Thru the snow, wind and cold, you stuck it out and it paid off.  Thanks for the report!
Way to go, that's awesome to see.  Joey
Nice fish, and good exercise for the day.
Emil you look warmer than the last trip with big chev in your boat.Nice catch.Mike
good report
Nice fish. I'll be heading up soon also  dsn
Hey, that's a nice load of fish if.  I kinda figured it's hard walking out there with all the snow. You toughed it out and were rewarded nicely.
Hey......I think I've seen that little green hut before........too bad you can't zoom to the sticker on the door.....me and my bro are there tomorrow....tight lines all...

RIGHT ON GUYS,WELL AT LEAST ALL THAT HARD WORK AND THE WALK FROM HELL,   ALL PAID OF AND THE FISHING GODS WERE GOOD TO YOU,ENJOY ALL THOSE VERY TASTY WHITEFISH,THEY TASTE GREAT...COOL PICS AS WELL....CHEERS
Hey  Ice,      Way To go!!!!     Nice Fish,   Whenever you need a ride????
Hey Ice Fisherman,  skunked 2 weeks ago when i met you but looks like you did very well today- Congrats!  ~Ryan (J.Kimble)

RickOnt,  Great offer appreciate it Bud. And right on time too ;-) My legs and back don't like me much tonight...you have PM. Let's go out when you are free.  Chevy, ha ha....my cell phone has zoom but didn't think to use it....should correct myself next time ;-) Sorry we didn't get together today but we'll do it very soon I am sure. Good luck together with your brother. I told the whities to wait for you Bud ;-)  Mike, ha ha....you got it ...cold was non issue today for us...overheating was...expeacially on the way out...going back was better because it was against the wind cooling me off....  Clampet, got swety at times but didn't take anything off as I had no way to carry it. And yes my GPS showed more then 3km one way...so more then 6 round trip...I'd like to think I am in good shape but not as good as I used to be...time to seriously think about a snow machine soon ;-)  Cheers, Ice Fisherman

AttaBoy, Emil.  Very nice shooting,  it looks like everything came together for you guys.  I would think that the heavy trudging would not be the most worstest of your worries, you can slow down and it's only time and stamina.  The wind and temps, -18C and 12- 15 knots (30 Km/hr) o' fresh NW breeze, are another issue.  That's a -30C (-22 F) windchill thingamajigger, walking out and sitting out on the open lake.   That is brisk fer sure.  Congratulations on a great day, you guys earned that one.  That was hardcore.
Great Report... First one with lots of whities I have read in a while....
HA!  That day prolly would've killed me! I'd have been a frozen "Lump", prolly on the way out... y'all done good!  Excellent report and those are the best cell phone pics I've ever seen.

Now that was certainly worth the hike Emil.  Congrats on a great day.     Hopefully Headhunter and I will have similar success on Saturday.  We'll be taking the sled and the new clam though.  Oh ya, note to self -  don't forget the heater.  lol  If your looking for a ride sometime give me a shut.  Fishnsled
nice report, and thanks for sharing. Looks like some tasty fish.
nicee report!
Good Job Emil
nice...  your cell phone takes better pictures than my camera.

At least you got out and got to fish.... Good on you.  We went out, it was snowing, but it didn't seem that bad from shore.. we got going out, once past the huts, We couldn't see anything... I was getting scared and asked Chuck to stop and check the gps... He said we were further way then the last time we stopped, he had no idea where we were. even with the gps... so we turned around and followed the tracks back...  We did get to help a couple, in a mini van, get back to shore...  Glad to see u had a good day out...  Safe Fishing First...  Lady...
Nice fish. W2G, Looks cold out there .    jordan
